summary: Interesting perspective about how BW is a deconstruction of deconstructions  in general. But you truly haven't heard how BW is...
question: Interesting perspective about how BW is a deconstruction of deconstructions  in general. But you truly haven't heard how BW is called a decon by the fandom? And to be fair BW does truly take apart certain conventions in the franchise without reconstructing them such as the title of champion. I will always love the fact the story ends without you being champion, and reduces it to a side quest. i guess TLJ ends happier because RJ wanted it to be easier on the next guy working on 9.
answer:
I drifted away from the Pokemon fandom and only recently gotten back into it, so I haven’t, haha.

True, I did like that! Or how SM sets you up as the FIRST Champion and all other League runs are people challenging you for the title, that was very cool.

summary: is there any way we can get an ADHD team rocket member bc pokemon is my new hyperfixation and I desperately want to be cool and...
question: is there any way we can get an ADHD team rocket member bc pokemon is my new hyperfixation and I desperately want to be cool and similar to team rocket(what no I'm not gay for Jessie that's not the reason behind this)
answer:
Listen Jessie and James are both ADHD. Here are some facts:

ADHD Jessie from Pokemon!

ADHD James from Pokemon!

  • Neither of them has very good processing speed and neither can let go of an idea once it’s in their heads. They also have trouble with logical steps, maybe an executive dysfunction thing, maybe a problem with their observational skills, but they tend to do the “step one, step two, ?????? step sixteen:  profit” thing for pretty much every plan they come up with.
  • Both very clever and come up with weird, innovative solutions to problems.
  • Absolute determination - once they set their minds to something, it’s gonna happen. It probably won’t work but it’s gonna happen. (re: all of their ridiculous and hilarious plans to Get That Pikachu)
  • Constantly defy the expectations that others have for them, whether on purpose or not. (Their boss wants them to be smooth and collected and successful at everything they try. Ash and his friends expect them to be ruthless and merciless, at least, they do in Indigo League. They both come from backgrounds which had specific expectations for them which definitely did not include joining Team Rocket.)
  • Putting them together was a really good move in some ways and a really bad move in others. They help each other cope with some of the trickier aspects of ADHD like RSD and bad memories, but also if they’re both having a bad brain day, that gets amplified above and beyond how bad it would have been for either of them solo.
  • Jessie’s RSD made her sharp-tempered, and she puts on an air of confidence to cover her deep insecurities. James’s RSD made him soft and kind in an attempt to never make anyone feel like he himself has been made to feel - especially visible in the way he treats his pokemon.
